This paper is primarily focused on recommendation systems, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category. The paper also discusses fairness and discrimination, which are topics that fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes measures to quantify fairness, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of diversity on users, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC) category.
